20.04.2025 Germany 🇩🇪 2 League.
After FC Köln received a €310,000 fine from the DFB last week for a large pyro show, around 200 masked FC Köln ultras climbed onto the fence in the second half. A banner was hanging on the fence with the inscription "your fines don't ignite, we do," and they acted as if the next big pyro display was about to take place. However, the Köln ultras only fired confetti and displayed the next message: "Not today, but soon, promise!"

12.04.2025 Austria 🇦🇹
Grazer AK with choreography in a home match against Altach

The figure you see is Dionysus, the god of wine in Greek mythology, who represents freedom and celebration.
A glass of wine in one hand, a football in the other, and a cigar in his mouth.

He is wearing a shirt with the club’s emblem, on which it says “20 years.”
At the center of the shirt, it says RED FIRM – the name of the club’s ultra group, which is celebrating 20 years.
(The Red Front).

On the banner below the figure it says: “Dionysus loves us.”
And in the third image it says: “And we love the red.”

The fourth and final image – another choreography from the same match.
A design that mimics an ancient Greek-Roman wall painting, with mythological scenes.

At the center of the choreography is the club’s emblem,
and the year it was founded: 1902.
Notice the wine jug, on which the founding year of the club – 1902 – is also engraved.

03.04.25 Netherlands🇳🇱
Starting this month, football fans with an area ban in the Netherlands will be monitored even more closely. The authorities of Leeuwarden (SC Cambuur) Rotterdam (Feyenoord) and Utrecht (FC Utrecht) will be allowed to use a new, portable device, the so-called Mini-ID, at home games of their clubs. The device, which fans are required to wear, allows the police to check in real time whether someone is near the stadium. Anyone who comes near despite an area ban will be immediately visible. For many people, this measure feels like a sliding scale towards a digital police state, in which people are increasingly subject to constant digital surveillance.
